<p class="p">At all latitudes, surface seawater salinity was fixed at 31 (practical salinity unit) and wind speed was fixed at 5 m/s, while sea-ice bulk salinity (
 <italic class="italic">S</italic>
 <sub class="sub">bu,fy</sub>) was computed according to the analytical function provided by (
 <xref rid="R55" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">
  <italic class="italic">55</italic>
 </xref>) for Arctic first-year ice, which is dependent only on the normalized ice depth (0 ≤ 
 <italic class="italic">z</italic> ≤ 1) and is based on a fitted salinity profile derived from a complex parameterization of sea-ice bulk salinity
 <disp-formula id="E1" class="disp-formula">
  <math id="m1" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">S</mi>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mtext class="mtext">bu</mtext>
       <mo class="mo">,</mo>
       <mtext class="mtext">fy</mtext>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">z</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mfrac class="mfrac">
      <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">z</mi>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">a</mi>
       <mo class="mo">+</mo>
       <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">b</mi>
       <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">z</mi>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
     <mo class="mo">+</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">c</mi>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
  <label class="label">(1)</label>
 </disp-formula>where 
 <italic class="italic">a</italic> = 1.0964, 
 <italic class="italic">b</italic> = −1.0552, and 
 <italic class="italic">c</italic> = 4.41272.
</p>
